
```
# 副簽
(pos:名詞)
<explanation>
yue:喺文件上做輔助性質嘅簽署，通常由副手或次要負責人簽名，以確認或核實內容（量詞：個）
eng:countersignature; a secondary signature on a document, usually made by a deputy or secondary person-in-charge to confirm or verify the content
<eg>
yue:呢份合約一定要老細同埋經理嘅副簽先至生效。 (ni1 fan6 hap4 joek3 jat1 ding1 jiu3 lou5 sai1 tung4 maai4 ging1 lei2 ge3 fu3 cim1 sin1 zi3 sang1 hau6.)
eng:This contract requires the boss's signature and the manager's countersignature to take effect.
``` [end of text]


